<title>USA: Franklin Ophthalmic in pact with lender.</title>
<headline>Franklin Ophthalmic in pact with lender.</headline>
<dateline>ROMEOVILLE, Ill. 1996-09-04</dateline>
<text>
<p>Franklin Ophthalmic Instruments Co Inc said Wednesday its principal lender, Silicon Valley Bank, agreed to convert about $3 million owed to it by the company under its line of credit into shares of Franklin Ophthalmic stock at $1.52 per share.</p>
<p>It said the bank also agreed to extend the maturity date on the remaining $1.8 million under the line of credit to August 1997.</p>
<p>The bank's agreement is conditioned on the company's receipt of at least $1 million in capital and personal guarantees (up to $200,000 in the aggregate) of officers of the company.</p>
<p>-- Chicago newsdesk 312 408-8787</p>
